From: Michael Schutte <michi@debian.org>
Subject: [PATCH] fixes/openvt_error_handling

Improved error handling for the openvt program.

This closes the Debian bug #190387.

Signed-off-by: Michael Schutte <michi@debian.org>

---
 src/openvt.c |    3 ++-
 1 files changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/openvt.c b/src/openvt.c
index 4f47ae7..7418daa 100644
--- a/src/openvt.c
+++ b/src/openvt.c
@@ -385,7 +385,8 @@ main(int argc, char *argv[])
 		close(0);
 		close(1);
 		close(2);
-		close(consfd);
+		if (consfd > 2)
+			close(consfd);
 
 		if ((dup2(fd, 0) == -1) || (dup2(fd, 1) == -1) || (dup2(fd, 2) == -1))
 			openvt_fatal(1, errno, "dup");
-- 
